>  <Product Name>  (97) 
Praeruptorin C

>  <Short Description for web display>  (97) 
1. Praeruptorin C has been widely used as an antioxidant and a calcium antagonist to treat diseases. 2. Praeruptorin C partially protects cortical neurons by inhibiting the expression of GluN2B-contai
ning NMDA receptors and regulating the Bcl-2 family. 3. Praeruptorin C can reduce vascular hypertrophy in isolated rat hypertrophied smooth muscle cells, and this is associated with improvement of smo
oth muscle cells [Ca2+]i level, nitric oxide content and cellular signal transdution of protein kinase C and Gi.

