EP2 receptor antagonist-2 (CID891729) is a compound that not only serves as an antagonist to the EP2 receptor, blocking its activation by PGE2, but also reduces lactate dehydrogenase (LDH) release tri
ggered by N-methyl-D-aspartate (NMDA).

