>  <Short Description for web display>  (233) 
Lariciresinol is an enterolignan precursor, it possesses fungicidal activities by disrupting the fungal plasma membrane and therapeutic potential as a novel antifungal agent for the treatment of funga
l infectious diseases in humans. Dietary lariciresinol can attenuate mammary tumor growth and reduce blood vessel density in human MCF-7 breast cancer xenografts and carcinogen-induced mammary tumors 
in rats.

