>  <Product Name>  (294) 
Liranaftate

>  <Short Description for web display>  (294) 
Liranaftate (Piritetrate) is a thiocarbamate and squalene epoxidase inhibitor with antifungal activity. Liranaftate inhibits fungal squalene epoxidase, an enzyme that plays a key role in the synthesis
 of sterol which is essential for cell membrane integrity. By preventing ergosterol synthesis and causing accumulation of squalene, this agent increases cell membrane permeability, cell leakage and ev
entually cell lysis.

