>  <Brutto-formula>  (296) 
C18H20N4O2

>  <Molecular weight>  (296) 
324.38

>  <Product Name>  (296) 
Nitracrine

>  <Short Description for web display>  (296) 
Nitracrine is a 1-nitroacridine derivative and is an effective hypoxia-selective agent in vitro and antitumor drugs. Nitracrine suppresses RNA synthesis and covalently, reversibly binds to DNA but als
o forms covalent adducts with DNA in vivo. Nitracrine has cytotoxicity towards most cells.

